rComments: He's a pretty good professor. There were a lot of quizzes but there are old practice quizzes online that are the exact same. It is the same with tests. I haven't done any of the homework this semester and I am doing pretty decent because I go to my discussion and I take these practice quizzes/tests. I would recommend his class.

He is the best professor I can ever imagine!  He is good at clarifying ideas, so you will definitely understand every knowledge after the lecture.  In addition, he is ready to help, so feel free to email him anything that bothers you!  The tests are very easy as long as you do the old tests and quizzes!  Strongly recommended!!!
Hard but fair. Excellent lectures and very helpful outside of class.

A good math teacher is a very rare thing. Prof. Murphy is a teaching diamond in a lot of rough out there. I would've taken Math 220 online if I hadn't been able to get him. You'll do well only if you do the hw and go to lectures AND discussion.  Be prepped for the 15 min. quizzes. Also, do not take without prior calc or precalc (Math 115).

Not sure why this class has such high reviews. Lectures are difficult to understand as he flies through material. Tests and quizzes are impossible. Puts terribly intricate problems on tests and quizzes that make your head spin.

Love him so much!!! With an easygoing disposition .Explains calculus clearly in each lecture and has his own class Syllabus, which tells  what u r supposed to learn and what the tough part is in each lecture. Gives a guidance about what to read! Such an organized and inspirational guy!Take his class!
Great professor, but likes to test students on the intricacies that are conceptually difficult.

Murphy is a great professor! His explanation is very clear and easy to understand. You can find lots of practice exams and quizzes in his website and they're very similar to the actual exams and quizzes. Tests are not that hard as long as you put in effort to do the practice exams.

Okay, of all the things you take from this review, just remember - *Do the homework.* Seriously. He gives you all the tools to do well, and just doing the homework and checking it over will make your test and quiz grades skyrocket. I got a D in the class the first time because I didn't do the work. Took it again and got a B+. Fantastic professor.

Murphy is a great person and a great professor. Tests seemed almost impossible. My advice is if you took calc in high school you might be ok, but if you only took pre calc and no calc, take this class at a community college!

The tests and quizzes ain't easy but he provided a lot of resources which means, you just have to work for it. The office hours really helped a lot.  The textbook are only useful to complete the assigned homeworks (which I don't think are essential to pass the class). Just do all the past tests and quizzes and you'll be fine!

The thing about Bob is that he doesn't give homework because he feels you don't need it to pass his class. Attend all his lectures because he gives the hardest examples of problems you can encounter and then breaks them down. I enjoyed the class and got an easy A- simply because I diligently went to lecture. Office hours  aren't necessary

For many people (at least for me), Calculus is a scary thing. Professor Murphy does a great job with teaching the course material. Unfortunately, he is aware of this, so the test and quizzes can be quite difficult. Just make sure you do the non-mandatory HW. The Final replaces your lowest test grade so make sure you study A LOT for it.
I did not go to class and that hindered me a lot. Go to his personal office hours, I have not heard anything good about the TA's. Do the assigned book work for practice.
challenging class, skips steps, goes by to fast
Very fair but strict in grading. Can get an easy B just by going to lectures.

Very difficult class. Even taking and passing AP calc in high school, this class was 10x harder. Half the class dropped out by mid-semester. Average grade of all 3 tests were D's. Very tough grader.  He claims that doing the homework is essential for doing well, but the homework never helps on the tests. Dont take! Take at community college!

Murphy is the math teacher I have ever had. He is a great lecturer, you need to work hard for the grade, but if you stay up to date and attend class you will be good. His previous quizzes are almost identical to the ones he gives out now. The prior exams also help a lot. One of the best teachers in the math department. You Da man murphy

I was new to Calculus when I took this class, and he made it very easy to get into it. I was not going to class enough by the end of the semester, so I got a C. Probably would have gotten an A or B if I showed up.

This class really makes you work for your grade. MURPHY DOES NOT CURVE.  Even with a class average of 50 there was no curve all semester.  Take advantage of the practice quizzes and tests online, they prepare you well for the real ones.  Lecture and discussion are not mandatory but it is very beneficial to go, especially lecture. Office hours OK.
